                <h4>U2 Required (15 credits)</h4>

    
      
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/econ-306" class="program-course-title">
              ECON 306 Labour Markets and Wages (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22350" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Economics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Economics (Arts)              : Examination of the implications on wage structures of differences in job conditions, levels and type training, long-term employment relationships, unionization etc. A variety of socioeconomic policy issues including subsidies for higher education, government regulation of workplace safety, and the role and treatment of women in today's labour force are explored.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Paul Dickinson (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Prerequisites: ECON 208 and ECON 209, or ECON 230D1/D2, or ECON 250D1/D2</li>
